└── .garden/          seed bank (dormant components — see below)
```

Tool config files at the root: `pyproject.toml`{% if programming_language in ['R', 'Both'] %}, `renv.lock`{% endif %}, `pixi.toml`, `environment.yml`, `dvc.yaml`, `.pre-commit-config.yaml`, `.editorconfig`.

## The Garden model — grow the project as you need

This template ships ~70 dormant components (data stages, language scaffolds,
infra subsystems, writeup formats, ...) in `.garden/components/`. Most stay
hidden until you grow them.

```bash
just garden                       # what's planted vs dormant
just garden-list dormant          # browse all available components
just grow data:features           # plant the feature-engineering data stage
just grow writeup:poster          # add a poster scaffold
just grow preset:bioinformatics   # plant a curated bundle
just prune <component>            # archive a planted component back to dormant
```

After scaffolding, the project starts with the components for your chosen
project_type (`{{project_type}}`) auto-planted via `just replant` (called by
copier after rendering).

## Get started

```bash
just setup                  # install dependencies (uv + pre-commit)
just tour                   # 5-line orientation
just doctor                 # check tools/state for currently planted components
just where <thing>          # find where X lives in this project
```

## Common workflows

### Exploration

```bash
# Create a new EDA notebook in stage 02
just notebooks new-eda "my-topic"

# List recent notebooks
just notebooks list-recent
```

### Data validation + profiling

```bash
just data validate-dataset path/to/data.csv
just data profile-dataset  path/to/data.csv
```

### Run pipelines

```bash
just pipeline                         # `dvc repro` for the whole pipeline
just pipeline-dag                     # visualize the pipeline graph
```

### Build the manuscript (if writeup:manuscript planted)

```bash
just manuscript-render
```

## Cross-platform commands

Most recipes work on Linux / macOS / Windows automatically. For paired
recipes that need explicit shell control:

```bash
just data validate-dataset           # uses bash on Unix, pwsh on Windows
just data validate-dataset-pwsh      # force PowerShell
just data validate-dataset-bash      # force bash
```

